topic.title: Hot-plug pins

body.p: For long term device reliability considerations, this section covers specific electrical requirements for Switchtec and its link partner (host, EPs). There are two main use-cases covered:

section.title: Hot-plug between powered switch port and un-powered link partner
section.p: The cumulative duration that Switchtec can tolerate a direct short to ground while the I/Os related to the port are powered on cannot exceed one week over the lifetime of the product.
For example, this scenario may result from a direct connection between a Switchtec port and an incorrectly plugged EP which shorts the high speed and/or sideband pins to ground.

section.title: Hot-plug between un-powered switch port and a powered link partner
section.p: There is no requirement on the high speed pins. However, for the sideband GPIO there are two categories:

li.p: Link partner signaling with a voltage high of > 1.98V
In this case, only GPIOs that are 3.3V tolerant can be used and the maximum time these IO can be connected to a powered link partner is 1mS
Link partner signaling with a voltage high of < 1.98V
In this case, all GPIOs can be used and the maximum time these IO can be connected to a powered link partner is 1mS
During the hot-plug event, current through the GPIO must not exceed 100 mA.
Maximum 100 mA current must not last for >100 ns cumulative during any given 1 ms period of hot-plug even signals in table indicating no support.
